The most relatable thing ever. I'm Australian so I went to an all girls school (super common here) and I miss that sisterhood every day. I went from being in a group of 10 girls (not even counting guys or floater friends) and we did EVERYTHING together for 5 years. We taught each other to drive, we lived with each other when our parents traveled, we had pot-luck lunches. My best friend really struggled in high school (she went to a different one) but now at uni she has this massive group and its like we flipped. I would give anything to find that again. I think it's timing as an adult though because making a strong friendship group work requires most of the group to be single. For both guys and girls, because then you're free like all the time. But that never happens because everyone gets into a relationship from being so lonely missing their high-school group.
